step_data.thought:
Looking at the current page state, I can see that I've successfully zoomed in multiple times, and the map is now at zoom level 14 as indicated by the URL 'http://127.0.0.1:3000/#map=14/42.8960/-75.1080'. The image tiles in the accessibility tree confirm this, showing URLs like 'https://tile.openstreetmap.org/14/4773/6026.png'.

At zoom level 14, the map should already be showing detailed road information including smaller streets and paths. However, since the 'Zoom In' link (bid 406) is still available and focused, I can zoom in one more time to level 15 to see even more detailed road information, which would show very fine details like building outlines, small paths, and potentially more road labels.

This aligns with the user's goal of seeing more detailed road information, so I'll click the 'Zoom In' button again to increase to zoom level 15.
